# Cortex local hard constraints
- Backend target is `daemon-rs` (Rust).
- Keep daemon endpoints localhost-only.
- Preserve zero runtime dependencies outside the binary.
- Keep embeddings in-process ONNX (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`, 384-dim); do not add Ollama/runtime embedding services.
- Keep conflict detection dual-path (cosine + Jaccard fallback).
- Keep SQLite as source of truth with parameterized queries; retain WAL setup in DB init flow.
- Preserve auth token + PID file behavior compatibility.
- Avoid `unwrap()` in handlers; return errors instead.
- Avoid `unsafe` unless explicitly required and documented.
- Do not add new crates unless clearly necessary.
- For `daemon-rs` changes, run: `cargo test`, `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`, `cargo fmt --check`.
